TITLE: Basic usage of Fuse.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This code demonstrates the basic usage of Fuse.js. It includes creating a Fuse instance with a list of items and options, then performing a search. The snippet shows how to initialize Fuse and use its search functionality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const Fuse = require('fuse.js')

// 1. List of items to search in
const books = [
  {
    title: "Old Man's War",
    author: {
      firstName: "John",
      lastName: "Scalzi"
    }
  },
  {
    title: "The Lock Artist",
    author: {
      firstName: "Steve",
      lastName: "Hamilton"
    }
  }
]

// 2. Set up the Fuse instance
const fuse = new Fuse(books, {
  keys: ['title', 'author.firstName']
})

// 3. Now search!
console.log(fuse.search('jon'))
```

