TITLE: Implementing Basic Fuzzy Search with Fuse.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the three main steps to implement fuzzy search using Fuse.js: defining the data structure, initializing the Fuse instance with search keys, and performing a search. The example shows searching through a book list with nested author information.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/README.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// 1. List of items to search in
const books = [
  {
    title: "Old Man's War",
    author: {
      firstName: 'John',
      lastName: 'Scalzi'
    }
  },
  {
    title: 'The Lock Artist',
    author: {
      firstName: 'Steve',
      lastName: 'Hamilton'
    }
  }
]

// 2. Set up the Fuse instance
const fuse = new Fuse(books, {
  keys: ['title', 'author.firstName']
})

// 3. Now search!
fuse.search('jon')

// Output:
// [
//   {
//     item: {
//       title: "Old Man's War",
//       author: {
//         firstName: 'John',
//         lastName: 'Scalzi'
//       }
