TITLE: Searching Object Arrays with Fuse.js in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to search through an array of objects by specifying which keys to search in. This example searches through 'author' and 'tags' properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/examples.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
[
  {
    "title": "Old Man's War",
    "author": "John Scalzi",
    "tags": ["fiction"]
  },
  {
    "title": "The Lock Artist",
    "author": "Steve",
    "tags": ["thriller"]
  }
