TITLE: Creating and Using a Fuse Index in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to pre-generate a Fuse index from a list and pass it directly to a Fuse instance to improve initialization performance for large datasets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/indexing.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const options = { keys: ['title', 'author.firstName'] }

// Create the Fuse index
const myIndex = Fuse.createIndex(options.keys, books)
// initialize Fuse with the index
const fuse = new Fuse(books, options, myIndex)
```

