TITLE: Nested Object Search with Dot Notation in Fuse.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates searching through nested objects using dot notation to define the property path. This approach allows for searching deeply nested properties.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/examples.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
[
  {
    "title": "Old Man's War",
    "author": {
      "name": "John Scalzi",
      "tags": [
        {
          "value": "American"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  {
    "title": "The Lock Artist",
    "author": {
      "name": "Steve Hamilton",
      "tags": [
        {
          "value": "English"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
]
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const options = {
  includeScore: true,
  keys: ['author.tags.value']
}

const fuse = new Fuse(list, options)

const result = fuse.search('engsh')
```

