TITLE: Nested Object Search with Custom Get Function in Fuse.js
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates using a custom getFn function to extract values from complex objects for searching. This provides maximum flexibility for accessing nested data.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/examples.md#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const options = {
  includeScore: true,
  keys: [
    { name: 'title', getFn: (book) => book.title },
    { name: 'authorName', getFn: (book) => book.author.name }
  ]
})

const fuse = new Fuse(list, options)

const result = fuse.search({ authorName: 'Steve' })
```

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
[
  {
    "item": {
      "title": "The Lock Artist",
      "author": {
        "name": "Steve Hamilton",
        "tags": [
          {
            "value": "English"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    "refIndex": 1,
    "score": 0.4
  }
]
```

