TITLE: Setting Collection in Fuse.js
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the setCollection method to replace the entire collection of documents in Fuse.js. If no index is provided, one will be generated automatically.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/methods.md#2025-04-17_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fruits = ['apple', 'orange']
const fuse = new Fuse(fruits)

fuse.setCollection(['banana', 'pear'])
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Adding Documents to Fuse.js Collection
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of the add method to append a new document to the existing collection in Fuse.js. The example shows how to add a new fruit to the list.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/methods.md#2025-04-17_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fruits = ['apple', 'orange']
const fuse = new Fuse(fruits)

fuse.add('banana')

console.log(fruits.length)
// => 3
```

