TITLE: Removing Documents from Fuse.js Collection
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates the usage of the remove method in Fuse.js. This method removes all documents that match a given predicate and returns an array of removed items. The predicate function receives each document and its index as arguments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/methods.md#2025-04-17_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fruits = ['apple', 'orange', 'banana', 'pear']
const fuse = new Fuse(fruits)

const results = fuse.remove((doc) => {
  return doc === 'banana' || doc === 'pear'
})

console.log(fruits.length)
// => 2

console.log(results)
// => ['banana', 'pear']
```

----------------------------------------

TITLE: Removing Document at Specific Index in Fuse.js
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use the removeAt method in Fuse.js to remove a document at a specified index from the collection. The example demonstrates removing the second item from a list of fruits.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/methods.md#2025-04-17_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fruits = ['apple', 'orange', 'banana', 'pear']
const fuse = new Fuse(fruits)

fuse.removeAt(1)

console.log(fruits)
// => ['apple', 'banana', 'pear']
```

