TITLE: Retrieving Fuse.js Index
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the getIndex method to retrieve the generated Fuse index. The example shows how to get the size of the index, which represents the number of documents in the collection.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/methods.md#2025-04-17_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const fruits = ['apple', 'orange', 'banana', 'pear']
const fuse = new Fuse(fruits)

console.log(fuse.getIndex().size())
// => 4
```

