TITLE: Accessing and Extending Global Configuration in Fuse.js
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to access Fuse's global configuration and extend its functionality. The code shows customizing the getFn option by first using the default get function from the global config and then potentially modifying its behavior.
SOURCE: https://github.com/krisk/fuse/blob/main/docs/api/config.md#2025-04-17_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const options = {
  getFn: (obj, path) => {
    // Use the default `get` function
    const value = Fuse.config.getFn(obj, path)
    // ... do something with `value`
    return value
  }
}
```

